HEADWORD: Chickasaws
<hw>Chick"a*saws</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>;
<sing><it>sing.</it> <singw>Chickasaw</singw></sing>.
<fld>(Ethnol.)</fld> <def>A tribe of North American Indians (Southern
Appalachian) allied to the Choctaws. They formerly occupied the northern
part of Alabama and Mississippi, but now live in the Indian
Territory.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

